Name: Thorium bundled ChromeOS Widevine CDM payloads
Short Name: ChromeOS Widevine CDM payloads
URL: https://www.widevine.com
Version: architecture-specific
Revision: N/A
Update Mechanism: Manual
License: By exception only
License File: x64/LICENSE
Security Critical: yes
Shipped: yes
License Android Compatible: no

Description:
These proprietary prebuilt payloads support bundle_widevine_cdm = true in
ThoriumOS builds. They are maintained separately from the desktop Widevine
payloads and must not be replaced with Linux desktop binaries.

Provenance:
The exact ChromeOS recovery images used to obtain these files were not recorded
in the original commits. Based on their embedded Chromium OS build metadata and
historical use, these payloads are inferred to have been extracted from ChromeOS
recovery images. The ARM64 payload was also introduced as the real CDM behind
Thorium's historical Raspberry Pi compatibility wrapper.

Source recovery image: Unknown
Last runtime validation: Unknown

Redistribution:
Widevine CDM is proprietary software. These payloads must not be redistributed
without a separate license agreement with Google/Widevine. Availability in a
public reference repository does not grant redistribution rights.
The x64 and ARM64 LICENSE files have identical contents; x64/LICENSE is the
metadata reference for both payloads.

